---

### 6. FILE NAMING CONVENTIONS

**Component Files:**
- **UI Components:** `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/{name}.tsx`
  - Kebab-case: `accordion.tsx`, `alert-dialog.tsx`, `button.tsx`
  - Multi-part names use hyphens: `input-group.tsx`, `button-group.tsx`

**Example/Demo Files:**
- **Basic demo:** `{component-name}-demo.tsx`
- **Variant demos:** `{component-name}-{variant}.tsx`
  - Examples: `button-destructive.tsx`, `badge-outline.tsx`
- **Feature demos:** `{component-name}-{feature}.tsx`
  - Examples: `breadcrumb-responsive.tsx`, `button-with-icon.tsx`

**Block Files (page templates):**
- Named by use case: `dashboard-01/`, `login-01/`, `sidebar-02/`, `signup-03/`
- Each block folder contains:
  - `page.tsx` - main component
  - `components/` - sub-components
  - `data.json` - mock data

**Registry Files:**
- `_registry.ts` - must be in each category folder (ui, examples, blocks, etc.)
- Master registry: `registry.ts` (combines all sub-registries)
- Generated: `registry.json` (auto-built, do not edit)

---

### 7. REGISTRY ITEM SCHEMA (from `/packages/shadcn/src/registry/schema.ts`)

All registry items follow this TypeScript schema:

```typescript
// Main discriminated union supporting multiple types
export const registryItemSchema = z.discriminatedUnion("type", [
  registryItemCommonSchema.extend({
    type: z.literal("registry:base"),
    config: rawConfigSchema.deepPartial().optional(),
  }),
  registryItemCommonSchema.extend({
    type: z.literal("registry:font"),
    font: registryItemFontSchema,
  }),
  registryItemCommonSchema.extend({
    type: registryItemTypeSchema.exclude(["registry:base", "registry:font"]),
  }),
])

// Common fields across all items
export const registryItemCommonSchema = z.object({
  $schema: z.string().optional(),
  extends: z.string().optional(),
  name: z.string(),
  title: z.string().optional(),
  author: z.string().min(2).optional(),
  description: z.string().optional(),
  dependencies: z.array(z.string()).optional(),      // npm packages (e.g., "radix-ui")
  devDependencies: z.array(z.string()).optional(),   // dev npm packages
  registryDependencies: z.array(z.string()).optional(), // other registry items (e.g., ["button"])
  files: z.array(registryItemFileSchema).optional(),
  tailwind: registryItemTailwindSchema.optional(),
  cssVars: registryItemCssVarsSchema.optional(),
  css: registryItemCssSchema.optional(),
  envVars: registryItemEnvVarsSchema.optional(),
  meta: z.record(z.string(), z.any()).optional(),
  docs: z.string().optional(),
  categories: z.array(z.string()).optional(),
})

// Supported item types
export const registryItemTypeSchema = z.enum([
  "registry:lib",
  "registry:block",
  "registry:component",
  "registry:ui",
  "registry:hook",
  "registry:page",
  "registry:file",
  "registry:theme",
  "registry:style",
  "registry:item",
  "registry:base",
  "registry:font",
  "registry:example",        // internal
  "registry:internal",       // internal
])
```

**Registry Item Properties Explained:**
- `name`: Unique identifier (kebab-case)
- `type`: One of registry item types (most are `registry:ui` for components)
- `dependencies`: External npm packages (installed to user's project)
- `registryDependencies`: Other registry components this depends on
- `files`: Array of file objects defining what to install
  - `path`: Where in the registry folder the source file is
  - `type`: Registry type of the file
  - `target`: Optional destination path in user's project

---

### 8. KEY DIRECTORIES AND THEIR PURPOSES

| Directory | Purpose | File Count | Notes |
|-----------|---------|-----------|-------|
| `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/` | UI components | 53 .tsx files | Main component library |
| `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/` | Demo/example code | 237 .tsx files | Multiple variations per component |
| `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/blocks/` | Full page templates | 30 folders | Dashboard, login, signup, sidebar variations |
| `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/charts/` | Chart components | 73 folders | Recharts-based visualizations |
| `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/internal/` | Sidebar internals | 13 .tsx files | Advanced sidebar examples |
| `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/hooks/` | Custom React hooks | varies | Reusable logic |
| `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/lib/` | Utility functions | varies | Shared helpers |
| `/apps/v4/lib/` | App-level utilities | varies | `utils.ts` contains `cn()` function |
| `/packages/shadcn/src/registry/` | Registry schema & logic | varies | TypeScript schema definitions |

---

### 9. SUMMARY: WHERE TO ADD NEW COMPONENTS

To add a new component like "stepper":

1. **Create UI Component:**
   - File: `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/stepper.tsx`
   - Follow the accordion/tabs/button pattern
   - Use Radix UI primitive if available, wrap with Tailwind styling
   - Export all sub-components

2. **Create Demo/Examples:**
   - File: `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/stepper-demo.tsx`
   - Main basic demo
   - Create variations: `stepper-vertical.tsx`, `stepper-completed.tsx`, etc.

3. **Update Registry:**
   - Add entry to `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts`:
   ```typescript
   {
     name: "stepper",
     type: "registry:ui",
     dependencies: ["radix-ui"],  // if using Radix
     registryDependencies: ["button"], // if using button component
     files: [
       {
         path: "ui/stepper.tsx",
         type: "registry:ui",
       },
     ],
   }
   ```
   - Add entries to `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/examples/_registry.ts` for each demo

4. **Build Registry:**
   - Run: `pnpm registry:build` (auto-generates `/apps/v4/registry.json`)

---

